title: Global youth unemployment rate until 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Youth unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 11.
In general Youth unemployment rate has stayed the same over the Year.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 2010 and 2011.
The highest Youth unemployment rate, of value 13.2 was reached at Year 2016,  2017,  2018, and 2019
The lowest Youth unemployment rate, of value 12.8 was reported at Year 2011
